Nanci,
I used to live in Tampa, my brother and sister live in Tarpon Springs, my dad
lives in Dunedin. So, we travel there pretty often. LOVE Busch Gardens!
We would love to come visit, but our work will prohibit that right now.

messages.subject: Re: Getting together
messages.msgSnippet: Teresa, Unfortunately that s just not feasible right now and probably won t be for quite a while.  We are in the middle of some major interior remodeling on
messages.messageBody:
Teresa,
Unfortunately that's just not feasible right now and probably won't be for
quite a while. We are in the middle of some major interior remodeling on
our new home, and my husband is gearing up to start a major project at
work. We are also in the middle of an adoption homestudy (which eats up
time as well as money) and our new daughter (when she comes home) will need
to stay here for a while and settle in.

Maybe someone wants to come and see Yellowstone and Glacier Parks in the
spring?? Think Bison, Moose and Elk calving, wildflowers, bear cubs,
geysers, some snow...
That is, if you can stand the dust from our remodel. Anyone have teens or
pre-teens they want to bring to do interior sheetrock, electrical,
plumbing, painting and decorating or exterior landscaping? How about child
care? (LOL) As you can imagine, with the two babes underfoot, not a lot
gets done on the house in a timely manner!

By the way, any of you Floridians live near Tampa? I have a sister there
who is a doctor. :)

Nanci K. (harried and lonely in Idaho)
